00:08:09,652 --> 00:08:11,001
- Yeah.
- That seems like

245
00:08:11,045 --> 00:08:12,916
a pretty intellectual thing
for him to mention.

246
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,483
What was the context?

247
00:08:14,526 --> 00:08:17,312
- He had invested in a NuvaRing
competitor called Vag-a-Plug

248
00:08:17,355 --> 00:08:18,966
and was practicing
his sales pitch on me.

249
00:08:19,009 --> 00:08:21,011
- This is your first argument?
Your opening statement?

250
00:08:21,055 --> 00:08:22,056
- Point to Amy.

251
00:08:22,099 --> 00:08:23,492
- All right, fine.
Forget the study.

252
00:08:23,535 --> 00:08:25,276
I just don't want to lose
what we already have.

253
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,496
- Ask anyone with children
and they'll tell you

254
00:08:27,539 --> 00:08:30,586
children bring meaning and love
into your life.

255
00:08:30,629 --> 00:08:32,849
Yes, there may be some moments
that you lose,

256
00:08:32,893 --> 00:08:34,851
but there will also be
new moments.

257
00:08:34,895 --> 00:08:36,287
Take the water park.

258
00:08:36,331 --> 00:08:40,335
I would never go with you,
but you know who would?

259
00:08:40,378 --> 00:08:42,598
Your kid.
- Point to Amy.

260
00:08:42,641 --> 00:08:44,208
- That's not your call to make,
Peralta.

261
00:08:44,252 --> 00:08:45,514
Point to Amy.

262
00:08:45,557 --> 00:08:47,472
- Okay, fine.
New subject: work.

263
00:08:47,516 --> 00:08:49,344
We both work way too much.

264
00:08:49,387 --> 00:08:50,475
Why bother having kids

265
00:08:50,519 --> 00:08:51,955
if you never get
to spend time with them?

266
00:08:51,999 --> 00:08:54,349
I mean, I love my job,
and I know you love yours,

267
00:08:54,392 --> 00:08:55,393
and I don't think it's fair
for either of us

268
00:08:55,437 --> 00:08:56,960
to have to sacrifice that.

269
00:08:57,004 --> 00:08:58,701
- Do you know why I want to
become lieutenant so badly?

270
00:08:58,744 --> 00:09:00,398
- To prove your worth to
your hyper judgmental parents.

271
00:09:00,442 --> 00:09:01,660
- Yes, obviously that.

272
00:09:01,704 --> 00:09:03,227
But also, the higher your rank,

273
00:09:03,271 --> 00:09:04,794
the more control
over your hours.

274
00:09:04,837 --> 00:09:06,970
Plenty of people
have jobs and kids, Jake,

275
00:09:07,014 --> 00:09:08,450
and they find a way.

276
00:09:08,493 --> 00:09:09,973
- This has become more about
your employment status.

277
00:09:10,017 --> 00:09:12,802
As your supervisor, I feel
I have a conflict of interest

278
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:14,369
and should abstain
from judging.

279
00:09:14,412 --> 00:09:15,979
- Okay, so do we both
get a point?

280
00:09:16,023 --> 00:09:18,155
- No. Kevin has been
on the phone all this time.

281
00:09:18,199 --> 00:09:20,201
He's also a licensed
debate moderator.

282
00:09:20,244 --> 00:09:22,855
- License number
J as in Juliet, 2-5-9...

283
00:09:22,899 --> 00:09:24,640
- This means nothing to me.
- H as in hotel.

284
00:09:24,683 --> 00:09:26,381
Z as in Zulu.
- Oh, thank God he stopped.

285
00:09:26,424 --> 00:09:27,686
- 3-6-9.

286
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:29,558
Point to Amy.
- Okay, fine.

287
00:09:29,601 --> 00:09:33,170
You want to know why I really
don't want to have children?

288
00:09:33,214 --> 00:09:35,346
I had a crappy dad.

289
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:37,218
I know what happens
when you mess up as a parent.

290
00:09:37,261 --> 00:09:38,741
It's not great.

291
00:09:38,784 --> 00:09:41,570
And this may come as a shock
to you, but...

292
00:09:41,613 --> 00:09:43,311
I kind of have some dad issues
with certain people.

293
00:09:43,354 --> 00:09:44,442
- Holt.
- Me.

294
00:09:44,486 --> 00:09:45,922
- Raymond.
- Yeah, but not just him.

295
00:09:45,966 --> 00:09:48,446
It's every male authority
figure from my entire life.

296
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:50,231
- Hey, Jake, can you move
"Legends of the Fall"

297
00:09:50,274 --> 00:09:51,319
from new releases into drama?

298
00:09:51,362 --> 00:09:52,407
- You got it, Dad.

299
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:54,409
Craig was only six weeks older
than me.

300
00:09:54,452 --> 00:09:55,758
- Since this has become
about me,

301
00:09:55,801 --> 00:09:57,629
I'm gonna have to abstain
from this round as well,

302
00:09:57,673 --> 00:09:59,240
but Kevin is still standing by.

303
00:09:59,283 --> 00:10:00,893
- Actually, I feel as though
your personal relationship

304
00:10:00,937 --> 00:10:02,591
with Peralta
affects me too.

305
00:10:02,634 --> 00:10:04,419
Luckily, I had Gail
standing by as well.

306
00:10:04,462 --> 00:10:06,029
- Oh, my God,
you guys know Gail?

307
00:10:06,073 --> 00:10:07,248
- Who's Gail?

308
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:08,292
- Vice president
of the Debaters Club.

309
00:10:08,336 --> 00:10:09,902
- This is a very big deal.

310
00:10:09,946 --> 00:10:11,078
- Do you need to hear
my credentials?

311
00:10:11,121 --> 00:10:13,254
License number
U as in uniform, 7—

312
00:10:13,297 --> 00:10:15,473
- No!
No more credentials, please.

313
00:10:15,517 --> 00:10:16,866
I don't want to have
a structured debate.

314
00:10:16,909 --> 00:10:18,520
It's an idiotic way
to decide something.

315
00:10:18,563 --> 00:10:19,521
- What?
- How dare you?

316
00:10:19,564 --> 00:10:20,826
- Is he insane?

317
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,306
- Raymond, Kevin,
I'll be reporting this.

318
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:23,525
- Okay, look.

319
00:10:23,568 --> 00:10:26,745
Amy, I'm scared, okay?

320
00:10:26,789 --> 00:10:28,269
I'm scared that
we're gonna have a child

321
00:10:28,312 --> 00:10:29,574
and I won't be able
to handle it,

322
00:10:29,618 --> 00:10:31,098
I'm scared that
I'm not gonna be a good father,

323
00:10:31,141 --> 00:10:34,275
and I'm scared that I'll make
a mistake I can't take back.

324
00:10:34,318 --> 00:10:36,973
- Jake, I get it.
I'm scared too.

325
00:10:37,017 --> 00:10:38,888
- Every other big decision
I've made in my life

326
00:10:38,931 --> 00:10:40,020
I was sure about:

327
00:10:40,063 --> 00:10:41,847
becoming a cop,
asking you to marry me,

328
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:43,980
buying those Jordan 1s
for $500.

329
00:10:44,024 --> 00:10:45,721
- Wait, you spent $500
on sneakers?

330
00:10:45,764 --> 00:10:47,549
- Yeah, they were so cool,
and if I had never worn them,

331
00:10:47,592 --> 00:10:48,854
they would have kept
their value.

332
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,508
- So they lost their value?
- Yes, all of it.

333
00:10:50,552 --> 00:10:52,119
I stepped in a puddle
as soon as I left the store.

334
00:10:52,162 --> 00:10:53,294
But this isn't about
the Jordans.

335
00:10:53,337 --> 00:10:54,773
This is about the fact

336
00:10:54,817 --> 00:10:57,211
that I don't want to bring
a human being into this world

337
00:10:57,254 --> 00:11:01,041
unless I'm 100% sure that
I'm ready to take care of it.

338
00:11:01,084 --> 00:11:02,825
Okay?

339
00:11:02,868 --> 00:11:04,479
- Too emotional.
Point to Amy.

340
00:11:04,522 --> 00:11:05,915
- Okay, Gail is clearly biased.

341
00:11:05,958 --> 00:11:07,482
I think we need
a new moderator.

342
00:11:07,525 --> 00:11:08,787
- Bob Templeman here.

343
00:11:08,831 --> 00:11:10,876
- What? How many people
are on this phone call?

344
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:15,403
- Hey, so Holt went to go
smooth things over with Gail.

345
00:11:15,446 --> 00:11:16,447
He thinks we may
just have to pay

346
00:11:16,491 --> 00:11:17,796
the Debaters Guild
a small fine.

347
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,885
- Cool. And as you can see,
Pam is here.

348
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:21,148
She has some thoughts.

349
00:11:21,191 --> 00:11:22,627
- I was saying to Jake,
before Bobby,

350
00:11:22,671 --> 00:11:25,021
I didn't think I wanted
to have kids either.

351
00:11:25,065 --> 00:11:27,154
But he's the best thing
that ever happened to me.

352
00:11:27,197 --> 00:11:29,112
- Hey, Pam, could you give us
a minute?

353
00:11:29,156 --> 00:11:31,419
- Oh, of course.
I'm gonna call my friend JoAnn.

354
00:11:31,462 --> 00:11:34,291
She's been waiting for
a big update on all of this.

355
00:11:34,335 --> 00:11:37,468
- Great.

356
00:11:39,514 --> 00:11:41,994
- I'm sorry.
The debate was a bad idea.

357
00:11:42,038 --> 00:11:43,518
I just...

358
00:11:43,561 --> 00:11:45,824
I felt ambushed by the fact
that you didn't want kids,

359
00:11:45,868 --> 00:11:47,478
and I thought I could fix it
with logic.

360
00:11:47,522 --> 00:11:49,001
- I mean,
what if I had won the debate?

361
00:11:49,045 --> 00:11:50,351
- Jake, I'm trying so hard
to be nice,

362
00:11:50,394 --> 00:11:51,874
but I don't know how to respond
to that.

363
00:11:51,917 --> 00:11:53,049
- Cold-blooded but fair.
- I get it.

364
00:11:53,093 --> 00:11:55,138
You're scared.
I can't change that.

365
00:11:55,182 --> 00:11:56,226
- Yeah, but that doesn't mean

366
00:11:56,270 --> 00:11:58,185
I'll never change
how I feel about it.

367
00:11:58,228 --> 00:11:59,577
I mean, I used to be scared
of sushi,

368
00:11:59,621 --> 00:12:00,883
and now it's my favorite food.

369
00:12:00,926 --> 00:12:03,015
I got tuna sashimi
from a pharmacy the other day.

370
00:12:03,059 --> 00:12:04,669
- You shouldn't have.
- Yeah, it was very warm.

371
00:12:04,713 --> 00:12:06,062
I got so sick.

372
00:12:06,106 --> 00:12:08,238
Look, can we just press pause
on this conversation?

373
00:12:08,282 --> 00:12:10,153
I mean, let's enjoy our lives
for a little bit,

374
00:12:10,197 --> 00:12:11,850
and then maybe the next time
it comes up,

375
00:12:11,894 --> 00:12:14,070
I'll feel differently, okay?

376
00:12:16,812 --> 00:12:18,161
- No.
- What?

377
00:12:18,205 --> 00:12:19,510
- I need an answer
from you now.

378
00:12:19,554 --> 00:12:21,033
Like right this minute?

379
00:12:21,077 --> 00:12:23,035
- You can take a day or a week,

380
00:12:23,079 --> 00:12:24,385
or maybe a month.

381
00:12:24,428 --> 00:12:27,214
- That's not a lot of time,
Ames.

382
00:12:27,257 --> 00:12:29,433
I mean, that doesn't seem
totally fair.

383
00:12:29,477 --> 00:12:30,869
- Well, now you know
how I feel.

384
00:12:30,913 --> 00:12:33,481
Women don't have the luxury
of waiting till we're 60

385
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:35,657
and then changing our minds
and getting remarried

386
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:38,007
and having a baby
with some dumb 28-year-old.

387
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:39,095
- Oh, come on.

388
00:12:39,139 --> 00:12:40,401
There's no way
I'm gonna be rich enough

389
00:12:40,444 --> 00:12:43,360
that a 28-year-old
is gonna want to be with me.

390
00:12:43,404 --> 00:12:44,622
Did that help?

391
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:46,189
Look, I don't understand
what the big deal is.

392
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:47,886
You're still young.
We have plenty of time.

393
00:12:47,930 --> 00:12:50,324
- I know, but I don't want
to wait around for two years

394
00:12:50,367 --> 00:12:52,195
and then have you decide
you don't want kids,

395
00:12:52,239 --> 00:12:54,980
'cause I don't want
to start over at 38.

396
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,983
- Start over?

397
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,159
Like, with someone else?

398
00:12:59,202 --> 00:13:02,727
- ♪ Casecation,
all I ever wanted ♪

399
00:13:02,771 --> 00:13:05,643
♪ Casecation, had to get away

400
00:13:05,687 --> 00:13:06,949
♪ Casecation

401
00:13:06,992 --> 00:13:09,081
♪ The vibe in here
is really weird ♪

402
00:13:09,125 --> 00:13:10,213
- I think they're having
a fight.

403
00:13:10,257 --> 00:13:11,388
- No, it's not a fight,

404
00:13:11,432 --> 00:13:13,869
it's just a devastatingly sad
conversation

405
00:13:13,912 --> 00:13:15,044
about whether or not
we should have kids

406
00:13:15,087 --> 00:13:16,350
or just start over,

407
00:13:16,393 --> 00:13:18,178
so you were totally wrong,
Rosa.

408
00:13:18,221 --> 00:13:19,440
- What? You got married

409
00:13:19,483 --> 00:13:21,181
without talking about
if you want children?

410
00:13:21,224 --> 00:13:22,356
- Yeah, and we also got married
without discussing

411
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:23,574
whether or not we like
water parks.

412
00:13:23,618 --> 00:13:25,097
A lot of new stuff has come up,
okay, Terry?

413
00:13:25,141 --> 00:13:26,708
- Why are you guys here?
- A CI came in.

414
00:13:26,751 --> 00:13:28,231
There's a lot of chatter that
whoever tried to kill Rojas

415
00:13:28,275 --> 00:13:29,232
is coming to finish the job.

416
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:30,320
- At the hospital?
- Yeah.

417
00:13:30,364 --> 00:13:31,843
Holt wanted extra manpower
here.

418
00:13:31,887 --> 00:13:33,889
- Okay, why don't you two
lock down the nurses' station

419
00:13:33,932 --> 00:13:35,238
while Amy and I
secure the room?

420
00:13:35,282 --> 00:13:36,848
- Actually,
I'd rather be with Rosa.

421
00:13:36,892 --> 00:13:37,893
- Uh-oh.
- Damn, Jake.

422
00:13:37,936 --> 00:13:39,590
Thanks a lot, Sarge.

423
00:13:39,634 --> 00:13:40,461
- You told me to sing!

424
00:13:40,504 --> 00:13:41,940
- Yeah, but what was all this?

425
00:13:41,984 --> 00:13:43,768
- That's just Terry
being Terry.

426
00:13:43,812 --> 00:13:45,161
- Okay, from this vantage

427
00:13:45,205 --> 00:13:46,684
we can see the elevator
and the stairs.

428
00:13:46,728 --> 00:13:48,947
No one should be able to get
to Rojas without us noticing.

429
00:13:48,991 --> 00:13:50,775
- Cool.
- Hey, look, um...

430
00:13:50,819 --> 00:13:52,777
I don't want you to get caught
in the middle of this stuff

431
00:13:52,821 --> 00:13:53,778
between me and Jake.

432
00:13:53,822 --> 00:13:54,997
I don't want you
to choose sides.

433
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,390
- Already chose. I'm with you.
- Really?

434
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:57,478
I didn't know you wanted kids.

435
00:13:57,521 --> 00:13:58,653
- I don't know
if I'll ever want kids,

436
00:13:58,696 --> 00:14:00,045
but you should have them.
They're so cute.

437
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,960
It's up.
- Aw, it is up.

438
00:14:02,004 --> 00:14:03,135
- Anyway, do you want me
to talk to Jake?

439
00:14:03,179 --> 00:14:04,876
I'm a pretty good bully.
- Thanks, but no.

440
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:07,488
I've got this covered.
I left him alone with Terry.

441
00:14:07,531 --> 00:14:09,054
That guy is
a walking advertisement

442
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:10,360
for the joys of fatherhood.

443
00:14:10,404 --> 00:14:13,450
- Do not do it.
- What?

444
00:14:13,494 --> 00:14:15,278
Don't you love your girls?
- So much.

445
00:14:15,322 --> 00:14:16,540
You should have seen Cagney
this morning

446
00:14:16,584 --> 00:14:18,412
with her little braids in.
- Oh.

447
00:14:18,455 --> 00:14:20,327
- But they are a ton of work,
man.

448
00:14:20,370 --> 00:14:23,286
If you are not totally,
100% sure you want them,

449
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,287
you won't survive.

450
00:14:24,331 --> 00:14:26,289
- Is it really that hard?
- Yes.

451
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:28,639
I never get any sleep.
I'm always sick.

452
00:14:28,683 --> 00:14:30,989
I never get to watch anything
I want on TV.

453
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,643
I still haven't finished
"Breaking Bad,"

454
00:14:32,687 --> 00:14:34,471
but I can recite "Moana"
from memory?

455
00:14:34,515 --> 00:14:37,561
"Maui, shape-shifter,
demigod of the wind and sea.

456
00:14:37,605 --> 00:14:40,172
I am Moana."
Why do I know that?

457
00:14:40,216 --> 00:14:41,391
- I don't want to watch
kids' movies.

458
00:14:41,435 --> 00:14:42,914
I want to watch movies
for adults.

459
00:14:42,958 --> 00:14:44,002
Adults and teens.

460
00:14:44,046 --> 00:14:45,656
- And they are getting
so manipulative.

461
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:48,006
Yesterday,
Cagney pretended to be hurt,

462
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:49,399
I went in to help her,

463
00:14:49,443 --> 00:14:51,662
and Lacey snuck in the kitchen
and stole two cookies.

464
00:14:51,706 --> 00:14:53,490
- Oh, my God.
Your children are monsters.

465
00:14:53,534 --> 00:14:54,926
- Hey, those are my kids, man.

466
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:56,101
Back off.
- Right.

467
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:57,233
- And the crazy part is,

468
00:14:57,277 --> 00:14:59,061
I really do want to go
to the water park,

469
00:14:59,104 --> 00:15:00,192
but I can't give that to him

470
00:15:00,236 --> 00:15:01,324
because it's the only card
I hold.

471
00:15:01,368 --> 00:15:02,499
- Mm.

472
00:15:02,543 --> 00:15:03,979
Elevator.

473
00:15:04,022 --> 00:15:06,242
- Excuse me, NYPD.
Can I see your ID?

474
00:15:07,896 --> 00:15:09,158
- Amy, behind the wheelchair.

475
00:15:09,201 --> 00:15:10,986
- NYPD! Stop!

476
00:15:15,251 --> 00:15:17,340
- Diaz for Jeffords.
- This is Terry.

477
00:15:17,384 --> 00:15:18,602
- I think we got our guy.
Colombian man,

478
00:15:18,646 --> 00:15:20,038
unarmed,
but he tried to run

479
00:15:20,082 --> 00:15:21,388
as soon as we identified
ourselves.

480
00:15:21,431 --> 00:15:23,041
And he's got a picture of Rojas
on his phone.

481
00:15:23,085 --> 00:15:25,217
- We'll be right there.

482
00:15:25,261 --> 00:15:27,045
- No one in or out
of this hallway.

483
00:15:27,089 --> 00:15:29,352
Why do you think that guy
is unarmed?

484
00:15:29,396 --> 00:15:31,223
- Who knows? Maybe he was
trying to smother Rojas

485
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:32,529
or unplug his life support.

486
00:15:32,573 --> 00:15:35,315
- Or maybe he's a distraction,

487
00:15:35,358 --> 00:15:37,578
and someone else is going
for the cookie jar.

