a mobster to help her family

554
00:17:40,744 --> 00:17:41,963
rather than a librarian

555
00:17:42,006 --> 00:17:44,356
whose bowels are tied up
like a sailor's knot!

556
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,228
- Okay, that's a very strong
argument.

557
00:17:46,271 --> 00:17:47,272
Very strong.

558
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,491
But you're forgetting
one thing.

559
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:50,058
You're not just gonna be
killing a mobster.

560
00:17:50,101 --> 00:17:51,494
You're also gonna be
killing me.

561
00:17:51,538 --> 00:17:53,714
- He said the blast would only
hurt people in the room.

562
00:17:53,757 --> 00:17:55,150
You could just walk right out
of here.

563
00:17:55,193 --> 00:17:57,892
- Pam, you know
I can't do that.

564
00:17:57,935 --> 00:17:59,720
Now, please,
just give me the bomb.

565
00:17:59,763 --> 00:18:00,982
- And then what?

566
00:18:01,025 --> 00:18:02,853
Bobby doesn't get any money
and I go to jail?

567
00:18:02,897 --> 00:18:04,159
I can't go to jail.

568
00:18:04,202 --> 00:18:06,335
Every roommate I've ever had
has hated me.

569
00:18:06,378 --> 00:18:08,511
In college, I had a roommate
named Mary-Ellen,

570
00:18:08,555 --> 00:18:10,992
and she was dating the brother
of Steve Guttenberg—

571
00:18:11,035 --> 00:18:12,080
- Pam, what are we talking
about here?

572
00:18:12,123 --> 00:18:13,647
- I'm sorry.
I'm really nervous.

573
00:18:13,690 --> 00:18:14,996
- Wait, wait, wait, wait!
I know it probably feels like

574
00:18:15,039 --> 00:18:16,476
