such a fancy prison.

589
00:18:48,290 --> 00:18:51,946
- With a lot of crafts?
- Yes, with tons of crafts.

590
00:18:51,989 --> 00:18:55,036
Pam, listen to me.

591
00:18:55,079 --> 00:18:57,908
Let's untwist this bowel
together.

592
00:18:57,952 --> 00:19:01,738
Let's clear everything out.

593
00:19:05,829 --> 00:19:07,918
- Okay.

594
00:19:09,746 --> 00:19:12,140
You did great, Pam.
Thank you.

595
00:19:12,183 --> 00:19:13,228
- Now that it's out
of my hands,

596
00:19:13,271 --> 00:19:14,795
I can see it really is a bomb.

597
00:19:14,838 --> 00:19:15,926
- Yes. Yes, it is.

598
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:18,538
- Oh, my God, get some help!
- Okay.

599
00:19:21,541 --> 00:19:22,716
- You okay?
- Hey.

600
00:19:22,759 --> 00:19:24,631
Yeah, I'm okay.

601
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,895
- Really surprised by Pam.

602
00:19:27,938 --> 00:19:29,897
I did not see that coming.
- Right?

603
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,028
You should have seen
the look on my face

604
00:19:31,072 --> 00:19:32,421
when I saw it was her.

605
00:19:32,464 --> 00:19:34,249
- Your jaw just dropped.

606
00:19:34,292 --> 00:19:35,511
- Oh, she's right there.
- Mm-hmm.

607
00:19:35,555 --> 00:19:38,122
- Good-bye, Pam.
Good luck with everything.

608
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:40,124
Kind of liked her in the end.
- Yeah.

